WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.880
And this is a continuation of our Wednesday evening series.

00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:07.920
We had taken a few weeks off, got back to it last week.

00:00:07.920 --> 00:00:10.840
And last week we looked at a text of scripture

00:00:10.840 --> 00:00:14.079
from the book of Genesis, El Roy,

00:00:14.079 --> 00:00:18.180
and the name of God that means the God who sees me.

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:22.399
And what a blessed truth that we can rest in knowing

00:00:22.399 --> 00:00:24.000
that God sees us.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:25.520
And I mentioned this last week

00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:27.879
that it's a comforting truth.

00:00:27.879 --> 00:00:30.959
It's also a convicting truth that God sees us.

00:00:30.959 --> 00:00:33.599
And we dealt with it predominantly

00:00:33.599 --> 00:00:36.599
from the comforting aspect,

00:00:36.599 --> 00:00:38.979
as we looked at that passage from Genesis 16

00:00:38.979 --> 00:00:43.060
with all the circumstances that were being experienced

00:00:43.060 --> 00:00:46.560
and how Hagar understood that God saw her.

00:00:46.560 --> 00:00:49.139
And so we're thankful for that Bible truth.

00:00:49.139 --> 00:00:51.279
As we come to Psalm 90 this evening,

00:00:51.279 --> 00:00:54.639
we'll look at another name that's given in the scriptures.

00:00:54.639 --> 00:00:58.040
Remember, we've said this in the beginning of the study,

00:00:58.040 --> 00:01:00.799
as we begin to look at the names of God.

00:01:00.799 --> 00:01:03.720
Our God is so great, He's so wonderful.

00:01:03.720 --> 00:01:07.000
There's so many attributes and characteristics

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:09.580
about our God that He wants us to know,

00:01:09.580 --> 00:01:12.480
that many of those attributes and characteristics

00:01:12.480 --> 00:01:16.080
are communicated to us through the various names

00:01:16.080 --> 00:01:18.559
that are given in the scriptures.

00:01:18.559 --> 00:01:21.120
And so as we know His name,

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:25.279
we'll put our trust in Him as we understand,

00:01:25.279 --> 00:01:28.440
through studying the word, the names of God,

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:31.000
it helps us to understand various aspects

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:32.599
of His nature and character,

00:01:32.599 --> 00:01:35.400
and it certainly strengthens our faith.

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:38.480
And the name for God this evening

00:01:38.480 --> 00:01:41.680
that's given here in Psalm 90, El Olam,

00:01:41.680 --> 00:01:45.760
and this name of God means the everlasting God.

00:01:45.760 --> 00:01:46.599
And look at it with me,

00:01:46.599 --> 00:01:50.319
Psalm 90 is believed to be the oldest of the Psalms.

00:01:50.319 --> 00:01:54.559
Moses is the human penman that God used to write this psalm

00:01:54.559 --> 00:01:57.599
and the psalm begins with a great declaration

00:01:57.599 --> 00:01:59.599
and a spirit of praise.

00:01:59.599 --> 00:02:00.839
Notice the Bible says,

00:02:00.839 --> 00:02:05.839
Lord, thou hast been our dwelling place in all generations.

00:02:07.400 --> 00:02:10.160
Before the mountains were brought forth

00:02:10.160 --> 00:02:14.320
or ever thou hast formed the earth and the world,

00:02:14.320 --> 00:02:19.320
even from everlasting to everlasting, thou art God.

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.720
Isn't that a wonderful start to the psalm?

00:02:23.720 --> 00:02:27.479
And you just see the high note of praise

00:02:27.479 --> 00:02:30.520
and just kind of begins with the crescendo, if you will.

00:02:30.520 --> 00:02:35.520
Lord, thou hast been our dwelling place in all generations.

00:02:36.399 --> 00:02:39.119
And so even as you read verse number one,

00:02:39.119 --> 00:02:42.639
though El Olam, the everlasting God is not mentioned

00:02:42.639 --> 00:02:43.520
until verse number two,

00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:47.119
you already see it being previewed in verse number one

00:02:47.119 --> 00:02:48.960
by the psalmist saying

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:51.880
that thou hast been our dwelling place,

00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:54.559
notice, in all generations.

00:02:54.559 --> 00:02:56.080
And so we look at verse number two

00:02:56.080 --> 00:02:58.520
and we begin to understand that he says,

00:02:58.520 --> 00:03:00.919
before the mountains were brought forth.

00:03:00.919 --> 00:03:05.160
And so God obviously is helping us to understand

00:03:05.160 --> 00:03:07.880
that these truths of creation,

00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:09.360
he'll say in the very next phrase,

00:03:09.360 --> 00:03:13.919
or ever thou hast formed the earth and the world,

00:03:13.919 --> 00:03:15.880
God is the creator.

00:03:15.880 --> 00:03:18.880
And the psalmist is acknowledging

00:03:18.880 --> 00:03:22.800
that before this took place, before the creation,

00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:25.759
and when we understand that the Bible says in the beginning

00:03:25.759 --> 00:03:27.639
in Genesis chapter number one,

00:03:27.639 --> 00:03:31.679
that's the beginning for us as far as time is concerned,

00:03:31.679 --> 00:03:35.960
our God has no beginning, he has no end, he is eternal,

00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:38.919
he is the everlasting God.

00:03:38.919 --> 00:03:42.399
And so we find that the psalmist here in Psalm 90,

00:03:42.399 --> 00:03:47.119
he begins to rejoice and to praise God for who he is.

00:03:47.119 --> 00:03:51.399
And he says, even from everlasting to everlasting,

00:03:51.399 --> 00:03:54.199
thou art God.

00:03:54.199 --> 00:03:55.320
He says in verse number three,

00:03:55.320 --> 00:03:58.720
thou turnest man to destruction and sayest,

00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:01.199
return ye children of men.

00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:04.039
And then notice this truth in verse number four,

00:04:04.960 --> 00:04:08.360
for a thousand years in thy sight

00:04:08.360 --> 00:04:12.600
are but as yesterday when it is past,

00:04:12.600 --> 00:04:14.880
and as a watch in the night.

00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:17.880
It reminds us of second Peter three in verse number eight,

00:04:17.880 --> 00:04:20.040
the Bible says that a day is a thousand years

00:04:20.040 --> 00:04:22.119
and a thousand years as a day.

00:04:22.119 --> 00:04:25.359
Why is it said that way in second Peter chapter three?

00:04:25.359 --> 00:04:27.959
Well, there are scoffers, mockers that are saying,

00:04:27.959 --> 00:04:31.399
where is the promise of his return?

00:04:31.399 --> 00:04:35.880
And the Bible tells us that the day is as a thousand years,

00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:37.119
a thousand years as a day,

00:04:37.119 --> 00:04:39.480
and then says the Lord is not slack

00:04:39.480 --> 00:04:42.040
concerning his promise to usward,

00:04:42.040 --> 00:04:43.559
as some men count slackness,

00:04:43.559 --> 00:04:44.959
but is long suffering to usward,

00:04:44.959 --> 00:04:47.000
not willing that any should perish,

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.119
but that all should come to repentance.

00:04:49.119 --> 00:04:51.959
And so we find this truth again,

00:04:51.959 --> 00:04:56.959
as the psalmist continues to focus upon this truth

00:04:57.279 --> 00:05:01.000
that our God is the everlasting God.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:02.000
There's a great contrast,

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:04.119
we're not studying the entirety of Psalm 90,

00:05:04.119 --> 00:05:06.200
but there's a great contrast with regard

00:05:06.239 --> 00:05:08.760
to the nature of our God,

00:05:08.760 --> 00:05:11.799
from everlasting to everlasting thou art God,

00:05:11.799 --> 00:05:15.000
the eternality of God is in full view and focus.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:17.239
But then we find that as we come to really

00:05:17.239 --> 00:05:18.799
verses nine through 12,

00:05:18.799 --> 00:05:22.920
we begin to see the brevity of life for us as human beings.

00:05:22.920 --> 00:05:24.679
You find in verse number nine,

00:05:24.679 --> 00:05:28.440
for all our days are passed away in thy wrath.

00:05:28.440 --> 00:05:33.440
Notice this, we spend our years as a tale that is told.

00:05:33.839 --> 00:05:38.480
The days of our years are three score years and 10.

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:41.720
And if by reason of strength they be four score years,

00:05:41.720 --> 00:05:43.880
it is their strength, labor and sorrow

00:05:43.880 --> 00:05:47.640
for it is soon cut off and we fly away.

00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:49.519
Who knoweth the power of thine anger,

00:05:49.519 --> 00:05:53.239
even according to thy fear, so is thy wrath, verse 12.

00:05:53.239 --> 00:05:55.839
So teach us to number our days,

00:05:55.839 --> 00:05:59.279
that we may apply our hearts unto wisdom.

00:05:59.279 --> 00:06:04.279
I'm not sure about you, but time is just marching on.

00:06:04.679 --> 00:06:07.279
I mean, it's not slowing down for anyone.

00:06:07.279 --> 00:06:08.559
You just begin to look at things.

00:06:08.559 --> 00:06:11.239
I don't know if you get memories on your phone as I do,

00:06:11.239 --> 00:06:13.399
if you take photos and all that sort of thing.

00:06:13.399 --> 00:06:15.640
And you get these memories that pop up

00:06:15.640 --> 00:06:17.239
and it will say something like this,

00:06:17.239 --> 00:06:19.399
on this day nine years ago.

00:06:19.399 --> 00:06:21.679
And then you look at that photo and you're like,

00:06:21.679 --> 00:06:23.880
man, that was nine years ago.

00:06:23.880 --> 00:06:25.480
And yeah, it was nine years ago.

00:06:25.480 --> 00:06:29.200
And we begin to be reminded of the brevity of life

00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:30.880
that God has for us.

00:06:30.880 --> 00:06:32.679
And there's a contrast here in Psalm 90,

00:06:32.679 --> 00:06:37.119
between our God, El Olam, the everlasting God.

00:06:37.119 --> 00:06:39.600
And then of course, humanity, frail human,

00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:43.799
70 or 80 is really the truth that we see in verse number 10.

00:06:43.799 --> 00:06:47.320
And we know that some have exceeded that 70 or 80.

00:06:47.320 --> 00:06:50.279
And I believe it was Dean that shared this term with me

00:06:50.279 --> 00:06:53.480
the most recently that I had recalled anyway,

00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:55.920
that he was on borrowed time, right?

00:06:55.920 --> 00:06:58.720
And it's one of those things that we understand

00:06:58.799 --> 00:07:02.359
there are those that live beyond the 70 or 80,

00:07:02.359 --> 00:07:05.880
but we see this aspect of contrast

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:09.679
between our lives and our God.

00:07:09.679 --> 00:07:12.760
I want you to consider with me in Isaiah 40 in verse 28.

00:07:12.760 --> 00:07:14.320
And then I'm gonna give you some truth tonight

00:07:14.320 --> 00:07:16.119
that I hope would encourage you

00:07:16.119 --> 00:07:20.480
when we consider the name El Olam, the everlasting God

00:07:20.480 --> 00:07:22.779
that is given to us here in the Old Testament.

00:07:22.779 --> 00:07:26.399
Notice in Isaiah chapter number 40,

00:07:26.399 --> 00:07:29.019
Isaiah chapter 40, and really in these few chapters

00:07:29.019 --> 00:07:31.140
in this section of the book of Isaiah,

00:07:31.140 --> 00:07:34.799
there's so many wonderful truths that are provided to us

00:07:34.799 --> 00:07:39.799
about who our God is and how he stands above

00:07:40.559 --> 00:07:44.380
the idols of the land and all of these so-called gods

00:07:44.380 --> 00:07:45.760
and so on and so forth.

00:07:45.760 --> 00:07:49.160
And if you're ever dealing with someone that's polytheistic,

00:07:49.160 --> 00:07:53.839
these few chapters in Isaiah are a great place to go to

00:07:53.839 --> 00:07:57.519
because it truly shows the God of the Bible,

00:07:57.519 --> 00:07:58.540
the God of the universe.

00:07:58.540 --> 00:08:02.119
But notice in verse 28, notice what Isaiah says.

00:08:02.119 --> 00:08:06.600
Hast thou not known, hast thou not heard

00:08:06.600 --> 00:08:09.880
that the everlasting God, the Lord,

00:08:09.880 --> 00:08:13.959
the creator of the ends of the earth, fainteth not,

00:08:13.959 --> 00:08:15.959
neither is weary.

00:08:15.959 --> 00:08:19.799
There is no searching of his understanding.

00:08:19.799 --> 00:08:21.880
Isn't that a great verse of scripture?

00:08:21.880 --> 00:08:26.760
I mean, our God is so great, he's so wonderful.

00:08:26.760 --> 00:08:30.440
He is the everlasting God, he is the creator.

00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:34.919
He does not faint, he does not grow weary, hallelujah.

00:08:34.919 --> 00:08:37.599
And the Bible tells us there's no searching

00:08:37.599 --> 00:08:38.479
of his understanding.

00:08:38.479 --> 00:08:42.400
Our God is omniscient, he has all wisdom and all knowledge

00:08:42.400 --> 00:08:45.559
and his greatness is known by us,

00:08:45.559 --> 00:08:48.760
but yet at the same time, we can honestly say

00:08:48.760 --> 00:08:52.159
that his greatness is unsearchable.

00:08:52.159 --> 00:08:54.760
And so we find this evening the declarations

00:08:54.760 --> 00:08:58.479
that we find in many more verses that we could go to.

00:08:58.479 --> 00:09:00.359
We'll look at some this evening

00:09:00.359 --> 00:09:03.960
as we go through the message about the declaration,

00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:07.880
the revelation to us that our God is the everlasting God.

00:09:07.880 --> 00:09:10.320
But let me just give you a few thoughts this evening.

00:09:10.320 --> 00:09:14.880
Because of this truth, I want you to rejoice and to rest

00:09:14.880 --> 00:09:18.119
in some of the ramifications, if you will,

00:09:18.159 --> 00:09:22.000
of the fact that we serve a God who is everlasting.

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:24.039
We serve a God who is eternal,

00:09:24.039 --> 00:09:26.679
who has no beginning and no ending.

00:09:26.679 --> 00:09:28.520
And I'll give it this way to you.

00:09:28.520 --> 00:09:32.359
Number one, because he is the everlasting God,

00:09:32.359 --> 00:09:37.359
he and he alone can make everlasting covenants.

00:09:38.200 --> 00:09:40.320
He's the only one that can make an everlasting covenant.

00:09:40.320 --> 00:09:41.159
Why?

00:09:41.159 --> 00:09:43.440
Because he's everlasting, he's eternal.

00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:46.880
And so the reality is that you cannot promise

00:09:46.880 --> 00:09:49.760
something to last even a day

00:09:49.760 --> 00:09:51.559
because you don't have the resources

00:09:51.559 --> 00:09:53.760
to ensure that it would be carried out.

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:55.880
But the reality is that you could never

00:09:55.880 --> 00:09:59.840
and I would never attempt to make some promise

00:09:59.840 --> 00:10:01.440
that would last forever.

00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:04.440
And so I want you to rejoice and to rest in this covenant.

00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:06.239
And I'll give it this way to you.

00:10:06.239 --> 00:10:09.239
Number two, because he is the everlasting God,

00:10:09.239 --> 00:10:12.239
he and he alone can make everlasting covenants.

00:10:12.239 --> 00:10:15.239
He and he alone can make an everlasting covenant.

00:10:15.239 --> 00:10:18.999
would exceed the days of our time here on earth.

00:10:18.999 --> 00:10:19.839
Why?

00:10:19.839 --> 00:10:21.839
Because we're not able to fulfill it.

00:10:21.839 --> 00:10:24.799
But yet we find that as we go to the scriptures

00:10:24.799 --> 00:10:27.439
that God tells us, the everlasting God,

00:10:27.439 --> 00:10:30.559
he tells us about some everlasting covenants

00:10:30.559 --> 00:10:31.679
that he's made.

00:10:31.679 --> 00:10:35.039
Let me begin with this one in Genesis chapter nine

00:10:35.039 --> 00:10:37.599
as we are reminded of the Noahic covenant

00:10:37.599 --> 00:10:42.399
and after the flood and all that had transpired,

00:10:42.399 --> 00:10:45.999
God destroyed, his wrath was poured out,

00:10:45.999 --> 00:10:50.279
Noah and his family are delivered from the ark

00:10:50.279 --> 00:10:52.919
and we find that they worship the Lord.

00:10:52.919 --> 00:10:55.799
And then in Genesis chapter number nine,

00:10:55.799 --> 00:10:59.279
we read of the Noahic covenant and we read this,

00:10:59.279 --> 00:11:02.459
I won't take the time to read the entirety of it

00:11:02.459 --> 00:11:05.219
for I simply wanna focus on some aspects

00:11:05.219 --> 00:11:08.719
of the covenants being eternal or everlasting.

00:11:08.719 --> 00:11:12.079
Notice the Bible says in verse number 12 of Genesis nine,

00:11:12.079 --> 00:11:17.079
and God said, this is the token of the covenant

00:11:17.079 --> 00:11:20.119
which I make between me and you

00:11:20.119 --> 00:11:22.759
and every living creature that is with you,

00:11:22.759 --> 00:11:27.759
notice this phrase, for perpetual generations.

00:11:27.839 --> 00:11:30.039
Isn't it amazing that our God can say that?

00:11:30.039 --> 00:11:33.279
It's because who he is, he's eternal, he's everlasting.

00:11:33.279 --> 00:11:37.919
And so he can say to Noah here in Genesis chapter nine,

00:11:37.919 --> 00:11:41.319
after the flood, he can say, I'm giving you this token,

00:11:41.319 --> 00:11:43.279
by the way, that's the rainbow,

00:11:43.279 --> 00:11:47.279
as we see in verse number 13, I do set my bow in the cloud

00:11:47.279 --> 00:11:49.679
and it shall be for a token of a covenant

00:11:49.679 --> 00:11:52.059
between me and the earth.

00:11:52.059 --> 00:11:55.639
But we find that as God makes this covenant,

00:11:55.639 --> 00:11:59.559
he makes it known that this is an eternal,

00:11:59.559 --> 00:12:03.379
he says, for perpetual generations.

00:12:03.379 --> 00:12:07.959
Though the name of God, El Olam, is not yet introduced

00:12:07.959 --> 00:12:10.479
to us within the writing of scripture

00:12:10.559 --> 00:12:13.559
at this particular time, we see the character

00:12:13.559 --> 00:12:15.759
and nature of God, that he's eternal,

00:12:15.759 --> 00:12:19.319
that he's everlasting, because he can say to Noah

00:12:19.319 --> 00:12:22.519
in this Noahic covenant, that it would be a covenant

00:12:22.519 --> 00:12:25.899
that would be for perpetual generations.

00:12:25.899 --> 00:12:28.179
Consider with me the Abrahamic covenant.

00:12:28.179 --> 00:12:30.559
Notice with me, we could look at a few different portions

00:12:30.559 --> 00:12:33.079
of scripture, but look at Genesis chapter 17.

00:12:33.079 --> 00:12:34.519
And in fact, if you were to study

00:12:34.519 --> 00:12:38.239
through Genesis chapter 17, you'll find that repeatedly

00:12:38.239 --> 00:12:40.319
in this chapter, there's the reference

00:12:40.319 --> 00:12:43.119
to the covenant being everlasting.

00:12:43.119 --> 00:12:44.899
And we'll just look at one verse here,

00:12:44.899 --> 00:12:47.959
but in Genesis chapter 17, in verse number seven,

00:12:47.959 --> 00:12:49.439
notice what God says.

00:12:49.439 --> 00:12:52.639
He says, I will establish my covenant

00:12:52.639 --> 00:12:55.799
between me and thee and thy seed after thee

00:12:55.799 --> 00:12:59.779
in their generations for an everlasting covenant

00:12:59.779 --> 00:13:03.999
to be a God unto thee and to thy seed after thee.

00:13:03.999 --> 00:13:06.639
Again, there's various aspects as you were to read

00:13:06.639 --> 00:13:10.679
through the entirety here of Genesis chapter 17,

00:13:10.679 --> 00:13:14.019
reference after reference with regard to the covenant,

00:13:14.019 --> 00:13:16.279
the Abrahamic covenant being that

00:13:16.279 --> 00:13:18.239
of an everlasting covenant.

00:13:18.239 --> 00:13:21.919
But why is it, how is it that God could make

00:13:21.919 --> 00:13:23.559
an everlasting covenant?

00:13:23.559 --> 00:13:24.979
Well, because he's eternal.

00:13:24.979 --> 00:13:26.959
He has no beginning and no ending.

00:13:26.959 --> 00:13:30.919
And so therefore, he can stand before Abraham,

00:13:30.919 --> 00:13:34.479
he can stand before Noah, and he can make this promise

00:13:34.479 --> 00:13:37.399
that is an everlasting covenant.

00:13:37.399 --> 00:13:39.599
Notice with the Davidic covenant

00:13:39.599 --> 00:13:41.999
in 2 Samuel chapter number seven,

00:13:41.999 --> 00:13:46.059
we find also a reference here in 2 Samuel seven

00:13:46.059 --> 00:13:48.659
with regard to the eternality of God.

00:13:48.659 --> 00:13:53.659
Again, this covenant is given in this passage of scripture.

00:13:54.439 --> 00:13:57.679
In 2 Samuel seven, remember David,

00:13:57.679 --> 00:14:01.559
he had a heart to build a house for the Lord.

00:14:01.559 --> 00:14:04.639
And in fact, when he first shares his desires

00:14:04.639 --> 00:14:07.599
to build what we would call the temple,

00:14:07.599 --> 00:14:10.319
we find that Nathan initially says go

